<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1040,1355]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1220,1246]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The forewing length is 
<quantity box="[584,662,1220,1247]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="22.0">22 mm</quantity>
in males and 
<quantity box="[814,892,1220,1247]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="23.0">23 mm</quantity>
in females. The detailed comparison of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1956" box="[1335,1437,1220,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis box="[1335,1437,1220,1246]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">P. hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[199,358,1256,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albosignata">
<emphasis box="[199,358,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">P. albosignata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is provided above in the diagnosis of the latter species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="25" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1040,1355]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,526,1292,1318]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">Distribution and bionomics</emphasis>
. The species is known only from its 
<typeStatus box="[938,986,1293,1319]" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">type</typeStatus>
locality in northern 
<collectingRegion box="[1214,1406,1292,1319]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">Yunnan Province</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[151,222,1328,1354]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="25">China</collectingCountry>
. The moths are on the wing in autumn, the habitat preferences and preimaginal stages are unknown.
</paragraph>
